problem:
What is the minimum number of small squares that must be colored black so that a line of symmetry lies on the diagonal $\overline{BD}$ of square $ABCD$? [asy]
for ( int x = 0; x < 5; ++x )
{

draw((0,x)--(4,x));

draw((x,0)--(x,4));
}

fill((1,0)--(2,0)--(2,1)--(1,1)--cycle);
fill((0,3)--(1,3)--(1,4)--(0,4)--cycle);
fill((2,3)--(4,3)--(4,4)--(2,4)--cycle);
fill((3,1)--(4,1)--(4,2)--(3,2)--cycle);
label("$A$", (0, 4), NW);
label("$B$", (4, 4), NE);
label("$C$", (4, 0), SE);
label("$D$", (0, 0), SW);
[/asy]

solution:
For diagonal $BD$ to lie on a line of symmetry in square $ABCD$, the $\boxed{4}$ small squares labeled $bl$ must be colored black. [asy]
for ( int x = 0; x < 5; ++x )
{

draw((0,x)--(4,x));

draw((x,0)--(x,4));
}

fill((1,0)--(2,0)--(2,1)--(1,1)--cycle);
fill((0,3)--(1,3)--(1,4)--(0,4)--cycle);
fill((2,3)--(4,3)--(4,4)--(2,4)--cycle);
fill((3,1)--(4,1)--(4,2)--(3,2)--cycle);
label("$A$", (0, 4), NW);
label("$B$", (4, 4), NE);
label("$C$", (4, 0), SE);
label("$D$", (0, 0), SW);

draw((0,0)--(4,4), linetype("8 8"));
label("$bl$", (0.5,1.5));
label("$bl$", (3.5, 0.5));
label("$bl$", (3.5, 2.5));
label("$bl$", (1.5, 3.5));
[/asy]
